Unidentified owl.  Seen at 10:30 in Dyea townsite north of the Warehouse, in fairly dense Sitka spruce / Cottonwood stand.  Only saw very briefly as it flushed from a tree and angled away through the spruce.  VERY BIG!  Initial impression was comparable to eagle size.  Dark in color, appearing monotone, but in poor lighting.  No ear tufts seen.  Wingspan an estimated 5 feet.  Extremely hesitant to say Great Gray Owl, but seemed too large for Barred Owl.  Size and no ear tufts seen nix Great Horned Owl.  Considering the Barred Owls known to nest near West Creek, this might be the most reasonable ID.
